docs.abstract: Eugene Scalia, whom Mr. Trump plans to nominate as labor secretary, has been a go-to lawyer for businesses like UPS and SeaWorld.
docs.snippet: Eugene Scalia, whom Mr. Trump plans to nominate as labor secretary, has been a go-to lawyer for businesses like UPS and SeaWorld.
docs.lead_paragraph: Eugene Scalia, whom President Trump intends to nominate as labor secretary, is often hired by companies when they are sued by workers, or when they want to push back against new employment laws and regulations.

headline.main: Trump’s Labor Pick Has Defended Corporations, and One Killer Whale
headline.print_headline: A Go-To Legal Hawk Is a Choice for Labor

docs.abstract: Today’s apps, services and hardware make it easy to jot, sketch and save the things that inspire you.
docs.snippet: Today’s apps, services and hardware make it easy to jot, sketch and save the things that inspire you.
docs.lead_paragraph: The need to take notes goes back through centuries of human history. It’s no wonder, then, that even the earliest desktop systems in the 1980s included a basic “notepad” program. But digital note-taking tools have been improving rapidly. Far beyond simple typed text, you can now save photos, audio and video clips, web links, sketches and more — all on your smartphone.

headline.main: Collecting Your Thoughts Is Good. Organizing Them Is Even Better.
headline.print_headline: Moving Beyond Pen and Paper. Way Beyond.

docs.abstract: Walt Disney’s grandniece Abigail Disney had said she was “livid” about the company’s pay practices after a visit to Disneyland last year.
docs.snippet: Walt Disney’s grandniece Abigail Disney had said she was “livid” about the company’s pay practices after a visit to Disneyland last year.
docs.lead_paragraph: LOS ANGELES — Walt Disney’s grandniece Abigail Disney, a critic of income inequality in general and the Walt Disney Company’s pay practices in particular, castigated the conglomerate anew on Monday, saying she came away “livid” about wages after a visit to Disneyland.

headline.main: Disney Calls Heiress’s Pay Criticism a ‘Gross and Unfair Exaggeration’
headline.print_headline: Disney Rejects Heiress’s Criticism of Wages

docs.abstract: “People who won’t walk across the street to save $5 on a pair of pants will take a day off from work to take advantage of a sales-tax holiday,” a tax expert said.

docs.abstract: Pressure from business groups — and the triumph of Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky over his junior partner, Rand Paul — spurred lawmakers to approve updates to the international treaties.
docs.snippet: Pressure from business groups — and the triumph of Senator Mitch McConnell of Kentucky over his junior partner, Rand Paul — spurred lawmakers to approve updates to the international treaties.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Senate voted overwhelmingly on Wednesday to approve updates to international tax treaties, some of which were negotiated in the early years of the Obama administration, in a bipartisan victory for multinational companies.

headline.main: Senate Approves Tax Treaties for First Time in Decade

docs.abstract: The five largest United States banks reported tax rates of 22 percent or less for the second quarter this year. Lower taxes helped smooth over some rough spots.
